Mitsubishi Heavy Industries Ltd &lt;MITH.T>said it began building the world's most advanced energy-savingtanker, which consumes only 48 tonnes of fuel oil a day.    Construction of the 258,000 dwt VLCC (very large crudecarrier) Nisseki Maru for &lt;Tokyo Tanker Co Ltd>, a shipping armof Nippon Oil Co Ltd &lt;NPOL.T>, is expected to be completed inApril 1988. It would run on the Japan/Gulf route, a companystatement said.    The statement gave no other details.    Mitsubishi Heavy last year finished building a vlcc ofsimilar size, but which consumed 57 tonnes of fuel a day. REUTER&#3;